  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health and Gender Support Project for Cox&apos;s Bazar District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to strengthen the integration of health nutrition population (HNP) services for the host community and DRP, IOM&apos;s operational activities under the Health and Gender Support Project (HGSP) investments will focus on improving the infrastructure at community clinics (CCs) and the District Sadar Hospital (DSH) and strengthening Government capacity to provide quality health care by providing qualified health staff for these facilities. In addition, IOM will operationalize a systematic referral system to support referrals from community clinics to higher-level facilities and strengthen community groups (CGs) for community mobilization to increase access to and utilization of HNP and gender based violence (GBV) response services. In addition, through this funding arrangement, IOM will cover the financing of operational activities for the third and fourth years of the ongoing additional financing (AF) of the Health Sector Support Project (HSSP) in Cox&apos;s Bazar, given that previously allocated AF funds for the third year have been reprogrammed towards the COVID-19 response. The ongoing activities undertaken through the HSSP AF to provide support to the DRP will continue for four years, i.e. the 3rd year (March 2021-February 2022) and 4th year (March 2022 - February 2023) of implementation of HSSP, using the financing of the HGSP.</narrative>
  </description>
